{{Infotable Bonuses|Mithril crossbow|Mithril bolts#Unpoisoned|Mithril arrow#(unp)|Mithril brutal|Mithril dart#(unp)|Mithril javelin#Unpoisoned|Mithril thrownaxe|Mithril knife#(unp)|sort=rstr|nototals=yes}}

==Armour==
'''Mithril armour''' is the fourth-highest quality [[armour]] in the standard spectrum of metal armours ([[Bronze equipment#Armour|bronze]] to [[Dragon equipment#Armour|dragon]]). Mithril armour requires 20 [[Defence]] to wear.

{{Infotable Bonuses|Mithril med helm|Mithril full helm|Mithril chainbody|Mithril platebody|Mithril platelegs|Mithril plateskirt|Mithril sq shield|Mithril kiteshield|Mithril boots|Mithril gloves|Mithril defender#Normal|sort=dslash|nototals=yes}}

===Usage===
Generally, mithril sets are considered fine armour with great protection for players sporting a low defence level. Since they are inexpensive and rather easy to obtain, mithril armour sets are used in the [[Wilderness]] even by higher levelled players. It also weighs less than other conventional armour.

==Other==
[[Mithril trimmed armour|Trimmed]] and [[Mithril gold-trimmed armour|gold-trimmed]] mithril armour have the same bonuses as standard mithril armour. These can be obtained from the member's only [[Treasure Trails]] minigame.

'''Note:''' Other players '''''cannot''''' trim or bless armour. Players claiming to do so are scammers.
